subject: Re: [junit] know any Metric tools?
msgSnippet: RSM at http://www.m2tech.net/ is a substantial metrics package.  It used to be shareware and is now commercial but has a free demo.  I used it for evaluation
messageBody:
RSM at http://www.m2tech.net/ is a substantial metrics package. It used to
be shareware and is now commercial but has a free demo. I used it for
evaluation purposes, so, this is not a recommendation just an awareness
sharing. It was easy to use and seemed to work well.
Regards,
Bill
